## PHASE 1: DATA MODELS (src/types/ifrs.ts)

### Core Entities

**CompanyMapping** - Master mapping saved permanently:
```typescript
interface CompanyMapping {
  id: string;
  companyId: string;
  companyName: string;
  glCode: string;              // e.g. "1001"
  glDescription: string;       // e.g. "Cash & Bank"
  ifrsLine: string;            // e.g. "financialPosition.assets.current.cashAndEquivalents"
  ifrsLabel: string;           // e.g. "Cash & Cash Equivalents"
  ifrsStatement: string;       // "balanceSheet" | "profitLoss" | "cashFlow" | "equity"
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}
```

**TrialBalanceEntry** - Monthly upload:
```typescript
interface TrialBalanceEntry {
  glCode: string;
  accountName: string;
  debit: number;
  credit: number;
  mappedIfrsLine?: string;     // auto-filled from CompanyMapping
  mappingStatus: "mapped" | "unmapped" | "new_code";
}
```

**IFRSStatement** - Generated output:
- Contains: balanceSheet, profitLoss, cashFlow, equity
- All amounts properly classified per IFRS standards
- AI validation included

### Balance Sheet Structure
```
Assets
  Current Assets (cash, receivables, inventory, prepayments)
  Non-Current Assets (PPE, intangibles, investments)
Liabilities
  Current Liabilities (payables, short-term borrowings, accruals)
  Non-Current Liabilities (long-term borrowings, deferred tax)
Equity
  Share Capital, Retained Earnings, Other Reserves
```

### P&L Structure
```
Revenue
- Cost of Sales
= Gross Profit
- Operating Expenses (employee benefits, admin, distribution, depreciation, other)
= Operating Profit
+/- Finance Income/Costs
= Profit Before Tax
- Income Tax
= Net Profit
```

